reviews.review_text: - The 2nd set jam starts with an extremely minimalist--almost desultory--Dark Star, and then crashes very unexpectedly into an MLB jam, something it seems like ages since they last played, and it kinda shows. The rest of Dark Star is pretty noisy & unmelodic, which, after so many shows that were very musical I thought I was looking forward to, but here they do it & it's kind of disappointing. I think even chaos is something you need to practice if you really want to do it well.
A Huge Improvement This is a very welcome upgrade to the previous SBD Master Reel > ? > DAT > CD-R.  This is a highly underrated second set.

good one I'm a bit biased toward fall 1973, and while anything compared to 11/11 winterland is a bit inferior, I'm going to take some issue with one of the precious reviews. Most obvious is that MLB was played just 6 days (10/19) before this show!
